    }
  }
  break;
```

The fix:
1. Checks the actual size of the `longBitmap.buf` using the `size` field
2. Limits the loop to the minimum of the buffer size and 8 bytes
3. Prevents accessing memory beyond the allocated buffer size

This resolves the stack buffer overflow vulnerability while maintaining the original functionality for properly sized buffers.
